comment: Smart (BOS) makes marginal contact with Williams (PHO) prior to the shot.
Ulis (PHO) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his drive to the basket.
Correctly called out of bounds.
Bledsoe (PHO) moves his pivot foot on the spin move.
Smart (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Bledsoe (PHO) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Williams (PHO) and Olynyk (BOS) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Williams (PHO) sets the screen on Smart (BOS) and absorbs the contact.
Olynyk (BOS) makes contact to Williams' (PHO) arm that affects his shot attempt.
LHH shows that Brown (BOS) clamps the arm of Warren (PHO), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.

Williams (PHO) is inside the restricted area when the contact with Crowder (BOS) occurs.
After communicating with the Replay Center, no additional penalties are assessed following a potential player altercation.
Smart (BOS) legally contests Booker's (PHO) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Dudley (PHO) commits a take foul on Brown (BOS).
Ulis (PHO) commits a take foul on Thomas (BOS).
Chriss (PHO) sets the screen on Rozier (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Chriss (PHO) is in a legal guarding position when Thomas (BOS) loses control of the ball.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Ulis (PHO) released his 3pt field goal prior to the game clock expiring is confirmed.
